                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12829712" author="jbellis" created="Thu, 4 Feb 2010 19:20:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The good news is this looks like a pretty harmless heisenbug &amp;#8211; eventually (usually the next timer iteration) no changes will be made to the map during iteration and it will work.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12842834" author="brandon.williams" created="Mon, 8 Mar 2010 22:47:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch to avoid concurrent modification.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12842835" author="jbellis" created="Mon, 8 Mar 2010 22:53:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;were you able to reproduce before, and not w/ this patch?  because AFAIK using an iterator manually instead of a foreach only helps when the CME is from modifying the collection in the same loop, and you can replace that w/ iter.remove().  otherwise if the CME is happening from another thread modifying stuff you have to move to a Concurrent collection.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12842845" author="jbellis" created="Mon, 8 Mar 2010 23:19:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;i think what needs to happen is take all the structures in Gossiper and make them Concurrent equivalents, encapsulate any places where we&apos;re returning them to other objects directly, and audit the rest for correctness, because the original author basically ignored threadsafety entirely&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12858686" author="brandon.williams" created="Mon, 19 Apr 2010 21:25:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch to use concurrent structures and remove synchronization  in the Gossiper.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12859836" author="jbellis" created="Thu, 22 Apr 2010 15:08:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Jaakko hasn&apos;t replied so I&apos;ll take a stab at reviewing.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Can you rebase?  2 hunks are failing in Gossiper for me.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12859981" author="brandon.williams" created="Thu, 22 Apr 2010 19:52:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Updated w/rebased patch.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12861487" author="jbellis" created="Tue, 27 Apr 2010 18:36:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;committed.  also inlined the comparator, replaced the last synchronized methods in EndpointState w/ volatile fields, and removed getSortedApplicationStates.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12889310" author="wadey" created="Fri, 16 Jul 2010 20:35:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This is a more serious bug than originally thought due to &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-1289&quot; title=&quot;GossipTimerTask stops running if an Exception occurs&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-1289&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-1289&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. When this exception gets thrown, it causes GossipTimerTask to stop running until the server is restarted. Because of this, I would recommend a backport to 0.6.x (I&apos;ll offer to do the backport as well). &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12889313" author="jbellis" created="Fri, 16 Jul 2010 20:40:55 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;backporting this to 0.6 doesn&apos;t work for me, but a hack to log exceptions would be ok.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
